For what ordered pair $(a,b)$ are there infinite solutions $(x,y)$ to the system \begin{align*}
2ax+2y&=b,\\
5x+y&=-3?
\end{align*}

The function $f(x)$ is graphed below.  Each small box has width and height 1.

[asy]
size(150);
import TrigMacros;
rr_cartesian_axes(-1,10,-1,10);

dot((1,7),red+5bp);
dot((2,4),red+5bp);
dot((3,1),red+5bp);
dot((4,8),red+5bp);
dot((5,5),red+5bp);
dot((6,2),red+5bp);
dot((7,9),red+5bp);
dot((8,6),red+5bp);
