For integers $n$, let \[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
n^2 & \text{ if }n\text{ is odd}, \\
n^2 - 4n - 1 & \text{ if }n\text{ is even}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f(f(f(f(f(4)))))$.

Let  \[f(x) =
\begin{cases}
k(x) &\text{if }x>3, \\
x^2-6x+12&\text{if }x\leq3.
\end{cases}
\] Find the function $k(x)$ such that $f$ is its own inverse.

Let  \[ f(x) =
\begin{cases}
-\sqrt[3]x & \text{if } x \geq 0,\\
x^2& \text{if } x <0.
