Hence, the area of $S$ is
\[\frac{4 \pi - \pi}{4} = \boxed{\frac{3 \pi}{4}}.\]

Let $E$ be the midpoint of $\overline{BC}.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E;

A = (0,0);
B = (sqrt(30),0);
C = intersectionpoint(arc(A,sqrt(6),0,180),arc(B,sqrt(15),0,180));
D = intersectionpoint(A--interp(A,(B + C)/2,5),Circle((A + B)/2, abs(A - B)/2));
E = (B + C)/2;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--D--B);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$D$", D, N);
label("$E$", E, N);
