Thus, the image of $4 - \sqrt{3} + (-1 - 4 \sqrt{3})i$ is
\[(4 - \sqrt{3} + (-1 - 4 \sqrt{3})i) \left( -\frac{1}{2} - \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} i \right) = \boxed{-8 + 2i}.\]

For $r = \cos 2 \theta \sec \theta,$
\[x = r \cos \theta = \cos 2 \theta\]and
\[y = r \sin \theta = \frac{\cos 2 \theta \sin \theta}{\cos \theta}.\][asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

real r, t, x, y;

t = -0.4*pi;
r = cos(2*t)/cos(t);
x = r*cos(t);
y = r*sin(t);
path foo = (x,y);

for (t = -0.4*pi; t <= 0.4*pi; t = t + 0.01) {
  r = cos(2*t)/cos(t);
  x = r*cos(t);
  y = r*sin(t);
  foo = foo--(x,y);
}

draw(foo,red);
draw((-1,-2.5)--(-1,2.5),blue + dashed);
draw((-1.5,0)--(1.5,0));
draw((0,-2.5)--(0,2.5));
